          "lecture_id": "differential_equations_001",
          "span": "Heun's method extends the forward Euler method with a predictor-corrector step. It first forms the Euler predictor\n\n\\[\n\\widetilde{y}_{n+1} = y_n + hF(t_n,y_n),\n\\]\n\nthen averages the slope at the current point with the slope at the predicted point. The corrected update is\n\n\\[\ny_{n+1} = y_n + \\frac{h}{2}\\left(F(t_n,y_n)+F(t_n+h,\\widetilde{y}_{n+1})\\right).\n\\]"
        },
        {
          "lecture_id": "differential_equations_001",
          "span": "An initial value problem combines an ordinary differential equation with an initial condition such as \\(y(t_0)=y_0\\)."
        }
      ],
      "rationale": "Heun's update formula explicitly defines the numerical solution update for an initial value problem, thus formalizing the concept of an initial value problem by providing a computational method to solve it."
    }
  ]
}
